00:03:05.352 --> 00:03:06.520
ASH
'Get back here!'

00:03:06.520 --> 00:03:08.255
Huh?

00:03:08.255 --> 00:03:11.024
‐ It's Ash.
‐ Give Pikachu back!

00:03:11.024 --> 00:03:12.826
[grunts]

00:03:12.826 --> 00:03:15.796
[all gasping]

00:03:15.796 --> 00:03:17.831
‐ Ah. Oh, no.
‐ Impossible.

00:03:17.831 --> 00:03:19.533
Ash disappeared into the mirror.

00:03:19.533 --> 00:03:21.468
[CONFUSED]

00:03:21.468 --> 00:03:23.136
But how could that happen?

00:03:26.239 --> 00:03:28.141
[panting]

00:03:28.141 --> 00:03:30.110
Ah. Ah.

00:03:30.110 --> 00:03:32.345
Huh? Where am I?

00:03:34.314 --> 00:03:36.983
[panting]
Pikachu!

00:03:36.983 --> 00:03:38.518
‐ 'Hey, Ash!'
‐ Huh?

00:03:39.853 --> 00:03:41.521
Well, well.

00:03:41.521 --> 00:03:43.657
[gasps]
Serena?

00:03:43.657 --> 00:03:45.826
‐ Where have you been?
‐ Huh?

00:03:45.826 --> 00:03:48.261
Just 'cause I called you
a crybaby..

00:03:48.261 --> 00:03:50.831
Who, me? Crybaby?

00:03:50.831 --> 00:03:52.833
Why are you talking like that?

00:03:52.833 --> 00:03:55.969
Look, it's Ash.
Brother dear, I've located him!

00:03:55.969 --> 00:03:57.604
Huh? Brother dear?

00:03:57.604 --> 00:04:00.474
[screaming]

00:04:00.474 --> 00:04:01.241
I went too far.

00:04:03.944 --> 00:04:05.746
Ash, we've been searching
all over for you.

00:04:05.746 --> 00:04:08.148
Huh? Awesome!

00:04:08.148 --> 00:04:09.950
I can't believe
how fast you've gotten, Clemont.

00:04:09.950 --> 00:04:11.651
Now, what do you mean?

00:04:11.651 --> 00:04:13.854
I've always been
the fastest runner.

00:04:13.854 --> 00:04:16.323
‐ I'm really good.
‐ You're kidding me.

00:04:16.323 --> 00:04:18.625
Never mind that. So where's
that Pikachu of yours?

00:04:18.625 --> 00:04:20.994
Oh, yeah, now, get this.

00:04:20.994 --> 00:04:22.996
Another me popped out
from inside the mirror

00:04:22.996 --> 00:04:25.499
then grabbed Pikachu
and ran off.

00:04:25.499 --> 00:04:26.967
[laughing]
What are you talking about?

00:04:26.967 --> 00:04:28.468
Was it a dream perchance?

00:04:28.468 --> 00:04:29.936
I was awake!

00:04:29.936 --> 00:04:31.805
So I jumped into the mirror

00:04:31.805 --> 00:04:33.940
and took off after the Ash
who grabbed Pikachu

00:04:33.940 --> 00:04:35.375
and that's when I wound up here.

00:04:35.375 --> 00:04:38.645
Hm..

00:04:38.645 --> 00:04:42.215
Hm, you are different than
the normal crybaby Ash I know.

00:04:42.215 --> 00:04:44.251
‐ Me? Crybaby?
‐ Huh?

00:04:44.251 --> 00:04:46.520
So maybe the culprit is..

00:04:46.520 --> 00:04:49.790
BOTH
Our crybaby Ash?

00:04:49.790 --> 00:04:51.892
Come to think of it,
there is a legend.

00:04:51.892 --> 00:04:54.494
‐ A legend?
‐ Correct.

00:04:54.494 --> 00:04:56.062
There's a famous legend
about the cave

00:04:56.062 --> 00:04:59.232
that lies right up ahead!

00:04:59.232 --> 00:05:02.235
You see, the legend states
for every crystal mirror

00:05:02.235 --> 00:05:04.971
in the cave,
there exists an alternate world.

00:05:04.971 --> 00:05:06.740
An alternate world
for every mirror?

00:05:06.740 --> 00:05:08.475
Right!

00:05:08.475 --> 00:05:10.243
And there's one more
important point

00:05:10.243 --> 00:05:11.244
but I can't remember it.

00:05:11.244 --> 00:05:14.314
Sounds stupid.

00:05:14.314 --> 00:05:16.616
Regardless, the Ash standing
right here in front of us

00:05:16.616 --> 00:05:18.318
'is not the Ash we know.'

00:05:18.318 --> 00:05:20.153
Huh?

00:05:20.153 --> 00:05:22.322
You know, as weird
as it's gonna sound

00:05:22.322 --> 00:05:24.357
I've got to admit
that the three of you aren't

00:05:24.357 --> 00:05:27.294
the Serena, Clemont and Bonnie
I know either.

00:05:27.294 --> 00:05:30.897
Hold on. I'm the only me and
anyone who isn't me is not me!

00:05:30.897 --> 00:05:33.466
Now, what in the world
did I just say?

00:05:33.466 --> 00:05:36.036
Whatever! Here's the deal.

00:05:36.036 --> 00:05:38.038
If you can beat me in a battle
then I'll have to believe you.

00:05:38.038 --> 00:05:39.239
Uh..

00:05:41.408 --> 00:05:43.777
‐ Okay. You're on.
‐ Huh!

00:05:43.777 --> 00:05:45.345
I like the kind of Ash
who would agree to accept

00:05:45.345 --> 00:05:47.013
a challenge from Serena.

00:05:47.013 --> 00:05:48.014
[AGREEMENT]

00:05:54.221 --> 00:05:57.090
Prepare yourselves for
a one‐on‐one Pokémon battle!

